based on the form of the expression SEXPR.  ENV represents
the environment in which SEXPR will be evaluated; it is a list
of the variable names.  When CPS initially calls CPC, ENV is NIL.
CONT is the continuation which will receive the value of SEXPR.
The double-quote (") is like a single-quote, except that
within the quoted expression any subexpressions preceded
by comma (,) are evaluated and substituted in (also, any subexpressions
preceded by atsign (@) are substituted in a list segments).
One special case handled directly by CPC is a quoted expression;
CPC also expands any SCHEME macros encountered.
